# =============================================================================
# Asperitas CODEOWNERS v3
# =============================================================================
#
# Status:
#   ACTIVE REPOSITORY OWNERSHIP BASELINE
#
# Purpose:
# - assign explicit ownership to governance, CI, packaging, source provenance,
#   biological evidence, rights metadata, retrieval, evaluation, security,
#   runtime, application, documentation, and community control surfaces;
# - preserve a repository-wide fallback so new files cannot silently become
#   ownerless;
# - make the highest-risk authority and certification files independently
#   visible during pull-request review;
# - support future delegation to qualified engineering, scientific, security,
#   legal, compliance, and product teams without changing path semantics.
#
# Current canonical owner:
#   @neo6bs988-dev
#
# Enforcement boundary:
# - CODEOWNERS assigns review ownership.
# - It does not by itself require approval or block merge.
# - Enforcement requires the active GitHub ruleset to require Code Owner review.
# - Ownership is not legal clearance, scientific validation, rights clearance,
#   security certification, deployment evidence, or production approval.
#
# Pattern rules:
# - GitHub applies the last matching valid pattern.
# - Paths are case-sensitive.
# - The global fallback appears first.
# - More specific authority surfaces appear after broader paths.
# - The CODEOWNERS file owns itself in the final rule.
#
# Truth boundary:
# - A tracked file may be documented, implemented, or tested without being
#   approved, deployed, operationally verified, or production-ready.
# =============================================================================


